title: Golden Gate National Recreation Area: Architectural Styles
body: A Guide to Architectural Styles at Golden Gate       Learn more about the different architectural styles and the architectural history of the park.         Overview to the Park's Architectural History         Greek Revival Style 1830s-1860s         Italianate Style 1850s-1880s         Colonial Revival Style 1880s - 1940s         Queen Anne Style 1880s - 1910         Mission Revival Style 1890s-1920s         World War II Temporary Construction 1938-1945
